description: Number of terms in A056761 [i.e. odd numbers from A056757] between 2^(n-1) and 2^n.
formula: Occurrences of odd integers x such that 2^(n-1) < x <= 2^n and the cube of number of divisors is larger than the number: A000005(x)^3>x.
example: A056761 is finite and has 267 terms. The last 4 terms arise between 524288 and 1048576: {675675,765765,855855,883575}, thus here a(20)=4. For n>20, a(n)=0.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Aug 16 2000
